-- Greek Minister Says Still Work Ahead as Troika Meets in Athens
-- B y   C h r i s t o s   Z i o t i s
-- 2012-09-09T15:13:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-09/greek-minister-says-still-work-ahead-as-troika-meets-in-athens.html
Greek Alternate Finance Minister
Christos Staikouras said there was “still work ahead” as he
left a meeting in Athens between finance ministry officials and
the so-called troika of inspectors from the euro area,  European
Central Bank  and  International Monetary Fund .  Finance Minister Yannis Stournaras is briefing the troika
today on 11.5 billion euros of spending cuts for the next two
years. The meeting is continuing. Stournaras is to brief Prime
Minister Antonis Samaras and the leaders of the two coalition
parties supporting Samaras’s government at 7 p.m. in Athens
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christos Ziotis in Athens at 
